\cf0 Yep, it is if you don't have any kind of documentation.\
But the flags can help you (ACPI_WMI_METHOD, ACPI_WMI_EVENT).\
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\sa320
\cf0 A debug option was added to wmi.ko last month, the module will dump wmi informations on load, and it uses wmidump output format. So you don't have to search _WDG in your DSDT.\
But even when you have found the correct UUID, you'll need to find/guess events code and methods id ...\
\
